fields.description:
I would like to report a *bug* when using Deltawalker 2.3.2 Oro with SouceTree 2.5.3 as external diff operation.
The settings filled in *Preference* - *Diff*- *External Diff - Custom | Diff Command | Arguments*  is just like indicated on DeltaWalker's website [https://www.deltawalker.com/integrate/other-apps] and SourceTree's website [https://community.atlassian.com/t5/Questions/How-do-I-add-DeltaWalker-for-diffs-in-SourceTree/qaq-p/111886]

But once invoking external diff in SourceTree(pressing CMD + D), I see following *problem/bugs*, that is * If DeltaWalker is alredy running, then everytime invoking external diff, DeltaWalker will prompt user that the revision to compare do NOT exist（and indeed the two revisions are not present/generated in SourceTree related folders）
 * If DeltaWalker is Not running, then DealWalker will launch and will successfully compare two revisions for this round of external diff request, BUT if invoking external diff in SourceTree again, DeltaWalker will prompt the same error as above mentioned (revisions not exist), this problem will remain no matter how many times one invoke external diff in SourceTree again UNLESS one exit DeltaWalker then invoke external diff again in SourceTree, then DeltaWalker will give a successful comparing on revisions, but invoking external diff in SourceTree again, DeltaWalker will fail to compare again.
 * Notes: When I check out the revisions files generated by SourceTree each time external diff is invoked in SourceTree, I find out revisions to be compared for DeltaWalker (and other 3rd party ex-diff utility) is located on my folder path below

{code:java}
/private/var/folders/3k/zrvyck5n78ndgg6vxjh61b7h0000gn/T/extdiff.<random-UID>/<1.Source.random-UID>
{code}
but the problem is the corresponding folder will only be generated ONCE when DeltaWalker is not running, once DeltaWalker in running, not matter how many times one invokes external diff in SourceTree for more version compare operation, the corresponding
{code:java}
.../extdiff.<random-UID>/<1.Source.random-UID>{code}
will not be generated again, instead these files in generated directly inside
{code:java}
/private/var/folders/3k/zrvyck5n78ndgg6vxjh61b7h0000gn/T{code}
folder as two files with following naming pattern
{code:java}
FileName_After_<after-revision-number>.txt{code}
and
{code:java}
FileName_Before_<before-revision-number>.txt
{code}
Above is the symptom for my case and I have seen other SourceTree + DeltaWalker ex-diff users have the same problem as well, as seen on the last comment([Sam Goody|https://community.atlassian.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/575066] [Apr 10, 2014|https://community.atlassian.com/t5/Questions/Re-How-do-I-add-DeltaWalker-for-diffs-in-SourceTree/qaq-p/111890/comment-id/11914#M11914]) from [https://community.atlassian.com/t5/Questions/How-do-I-add-DeltaWalker-for-diffs-in-SourceTree/qaq-p/111886]
 
So far my workaound is to enture DeltaWalker is closed everytime before I need to start a ex-diff in SourceTree, do my one time comparing in DeltaWalker then close it again for next round of SourceTree ex-diff, but this is great hassle and tedious. Particularly for users like me who need to do a series rounds of ex-diff inside SourceTree very often in one session.
 
I am not sure where the underlying problem is located, is it wrong with the argument I put in SourceTree(I follow the DeltaWalker webpage indication exactly), or is it a bug in SourceTree side, or is it with the system Mercurial. Please fix it.


Plus, I also wondered if DeltaWalker could be integrated into SourceTree as an officially supported ex-diff utility like FileMerge, BeyondCompare etc, since for many professional diff users I know of, they use DeltaWalker over other utilities. Please consider adding DeltaWalker support. * [https://community.atlassian.com/t5/SourceTree-questions/Feature-Request-add-integration-for-deltawalker/qaq-p/363857]
 * https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/SRCTREE-2046
 * https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/SRCTREE-2433?workflowName=SourceTree+Bug+Workflow&stepId=1

p.s. : From the posts above, I see there is an effot to add DeltaWalker as build-in ex-diff support back in 2011 but failed since DeltaWalker is not very stable back then, now the latest release of DeltaWalker is v2.3.2 in Apr 2017, during all this time DeltaWalker has gone through a series round of major upgrade in both functionality and core architecture, and it has been running so stable according to DeltaWalker community. So please give it another go and see if we get luck this time. ;P

Look forward to your kind assistance, since SourceTree rocks!

Thank you in advance.





--
Best regardsMilo
